pullRequest.title: timetracking: add compost bin time trackers
pullRequest.bodyText:
This adds compost timers to the farming plugin. I am only 99% sure of the tick cycles, the wiki is a very bad source of information and Mod Ash was unable to provide me a definitive answer. Per his tweets, he believes it is a 40 minute tick. I am very, very confident the timing of the supercompost for giant compost bins but less sure for regular bins. Wiki says the times differ, but this is not supported by what I have seen.
I AM confident there are two tick cycles for both giant and regular bins based on the varbits (two bits where the bin says the compost is rotting then a third bit where you can open the bin). There is a slight possibility that the regular bin is 2x20, but when I tested my plugin with that timing, the compost was never ready when the plugin said it would be.
This is the UI in the special tab of the plugin.

Fixes #2960
Closes #6569
